The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of automorphism groups and isomorphism testing suggests a connection to cs.LG (Learning), while the use of first-order logic and counting suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper also involves the study of graph structures and their properties, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
